The OISE GSA and AECD SOS are excited to invite you to our Crafting for a Cause Event!

Date: Wednesday, Sept 25th
Time: 3:00pm - 5:00pm
Location: Peace Lounge (7th floor, OISE)
Details: Tea & refreshments available!

Join us while we create and reflect on Orange Shirt Day, which is observed on September 30th. Orange Shirt Day has been observed annually for many years, and since 2021, has been formally recognized as the National Day for Truth & Reconciliation. 

We look forward to engaging in critical conversations around the topics of truth and reconciliation, decolonization, and Indigenous justice. We hope that you can join us. 

#TruthandReconciliation #OrangeShirtDay #IndigenousJustice #TRC2024 #TRC #OISEGSA #StudentsonSeven #AECD #AdultEducation #OISE #OISEUofT

Hello OISE students, 

Below is a message from The Varsity Reporter, Jessie Schwalb:

In April, OISE got hit with a ransomware attack that leaked SIN numbers for more than 8,200 students, alumni, and personnel. My name is Jessie Schwalb, and I'm a reporter from The Varsity who's looking into this attack. If you or anyone you know got an email telling you that the attack exposed your data and you'd be willing to speak a bit about your experience, please contact me at jessies@thevarsity.ca. Thank you for supporting student journalism!

Please contact @thevarsitypublications reporter Jessie Schwalb by SEPTEMBER 25 if the April ransomware incident impacted you or people you know! 
DM on IG: @j.smidgeon 
Email: jessies@thevarsity.ca
Thanks for supporting student journalism!

#OISE #OISEUofT #OISEGSA #StudentJournalism #StudentActivism #TheVarsity

🏃‍♀️✨ Join us for our Fall Term 5K Run Fundraiser! ✨🏃‍♂️

In collaboration with UofT Run Club, the Nursing Undergraduate Society is hosting a 5k run to raise money for Yonge Street Mission. Get ready to lace up your sneakers and hit the pavement for a great cause! Whether you’re a seasoned runner or just looking to have some fun, this event is for everyone. 🌟

📅 Date: October 5th, 2024
🕘 Time: 9:00am
📍 Location: 15 Kings College Circle, Toronto ON M5S 3H7

The registration fee is $5, where all proceeds will go towards Yonge Street Mission to help make a difference in our community. The run is not competitive, however, times of completion will be provided at the end of your run. Enjoy complimentary juice and snacks at the finish line! 🏅

👟 Sign up today and let’s run together for change! Tag your friends and spread the word!

🫶🏾🇳🇬Join us for the NSA Annual General Meeting! 🇳🇬🫶🏾

Come meet the NSA executive team, grab FREE food, and enjoy fun games and trivia! We’ll be reflecting on our accomplishments, planning for the future, and celebrating Nigerian Independence at this year’s AGM. We’d love to hear your thoughts on how we can grow together as a community! 🌟

Food, games, and great company – it’s the perfect way to kick off an exciting new year for the NSA! 🙌🏽🇳🇬
